    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 121,
        "summary": "1\u20136, The Prophet pleads with the Lord for the suffering Saints; 7\u201310, The Lord speaks peace to him; 11\u201317, Cursed are all those who raise false cries of transgression against the Lord's people; 18\u201325, They will not have right to the priesthood and will be damned; 26\u201332, Glorious revelations promised those who endure valiantly; 33\u201340, Why many are called and few are chosen; 41\u201346, The priesthood should be used only in righteousness.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "O God, where art thou? And where is the pavilion that covereth thy hiding place?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 27:46.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 13:1 (1\u20132); 18:11; 102:2; Isa. 45:15.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "How long shall thy hand be stayed, and thine eye, yea thy pure eye, behold from the eternal heavens the wrongs of thy people and of thy servants, and thine ear be penetrated with their cries?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 5:22; Ps. 35:17 (17\u201328); 89:46; Hab. 1:2 (2\u20134).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, O Lord, how long shall they suffer these wrongs and unlawful oppressions, before thine heart shall be softened toward them, and thy bowels be moved with compassion toward them?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 69:14 (1\u20132, 14); Alma 14:26 (26\u201329).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cruelty; Oppression; Persecution.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion.",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 168
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O Lord God Almighty, maker of heaven, earth, and seas, and of all things that in them are, and who controllest and subjectest the devil, and the dark and benighted dominion of Sheol\u2014stretch forth thy hand; let thine eye pierce; let thy pavilion be taken up; let thy hiding place no longer be covered; let thine ear be inclined; let thine heart be softened, and thy bowels moved with compassion toward us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:1.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 22:7.",
                        "start": 236,
                        "end": 244
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:89; 123:6.",
                        "start": 266,
                        "end": 278
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion; God, Mercy of.",
                        "start": 338,
                        "end": 343
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 240
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let thine anger be kindled against our enemies; and, in the fury of thine heart, with thy sword avenge us of our wrongs.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:84.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:13 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 35:1 (1\u201310); Luke 18:7.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember thy suffering saints, O our God; and thy servants will rejoice in thy name forever.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 122:5 (5\u20137). TG\u00a0Suffering.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, peace be unto thy soul; thine adversity and thine afflictions shall be but a small moment;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 23:11 (11\u201314). TG\u00a0Comfort.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adversity; Affliction.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 54:7.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then, if thou endure it well, God shall exalt thee on high; thou shalt triumph over all thy foes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 2:20 (19\u201323). TG\u00a0Perseverance; Probation.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Enemies.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thy friends do stand by thee, and they shall hail thee again with warm hearts and friendly hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 122:3. TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou art not yet as Job; thy friends do not contend against thee, neither charge thee with transgression, as they did Job.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 4:1 (1\u20138); 13:4; 16:2.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they who do charge thee with transgression, their hope shall be blasted, and their prospects shall melt away as the hoar frost melteth before the burning rays of the rising sun;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 58:7 (3\u201311); Jer. 1:19 (7\u201319).",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And also that God hath set his hand and seal to change the times and seasons, and to blind their minds, that they may not understand his marvelous workings; that he may prove them also and take them in their own craftiness;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 2:21 (19\u201322, 28); Acts 1:7; D&C 68:11 (7\u201312). TG\u00a0Time.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 6:18 (18\u201323). TG\u00a0Mind.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 8:19; 1\u00a0Ne. 19:22; Alma 23:6; D&C 84:3.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 155
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 169,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Also because their hearts are corrupted, and the things which they are willing to bring upon others, and love to have others suffer, may come upon themselves to the very uttermost;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 14:3.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 157
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That they may be disappointed also, and their hopes may be cut off;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 4:10.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And not many years hence, that they and their posterity shall be swept from under heaven, saith God, that not one of them is left to stand by the wall.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 37:28; 109:13.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 124:52.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cursed are all those that shall lift up the heel against mine anointed, saith the Lord, and cry they have sinned when they have not sinned before me, saith the Lord, but have done that which was meet in mine eyes, and which I commanded them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 41:9; John 13:18. TG\u00a0Prophets, Rejection of; Reviling.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 26:9; Ps. 2:2 (2\u20134); 105:15.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 15:20; Moro. 7:14 (14, 18); D&C 64:16.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But those who cry transgression do it because they are the servants of sin, and are the children of disobedience themselves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 12:10; Alma 15:15.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 5:6 (2\u20136).",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And those who swear falsely against my servants, that they might bring them into bondage and death\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Swearing.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mal. 3:5. TG\u00a0Lying; Slander.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wo unto them; because they have offended my little ones they shall be severed from the ordinances of mine house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 18:6. TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Ordinance; Salvation.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Their basket shall not be full, their houses and their barns shall perish, and they themselves shall be despised by those that flattered them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:17 (15\u201326).",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:24 (23\u201326).",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They shall not have right to the priesthood, nor their posterity after them from generation to generation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 13:4 (3\u20135). TG\u00a0Priesthood, Qualifying for.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It had been better for them that a millstone had been hanged about their necks, and they drowned in the depth of the sea.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 18:6; D&C 54:5.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wo unto all those that discomfort my people, and drive, and murder, and testify against them, saith the Lord of Hosts; a generation of vipers shall not escape the damnation of hell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:1.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 3:13.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 12:34; 23:33.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, mine eyes see and know all their works, and I have in reserve a swift judgment in the season thereof, for them all;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 10:4; Ps. 139:1; Jonah 3:10. TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 109:7 (3\u20137); Hel. 8:25; D&C 10:23 (20\u201323).",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For there is a time appointed for every man, according as his works shall be.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 122:9.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 7:1; Alma 12:27 (26\u201328); D&C 42:48.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "God shall give unto you knowledge by his Holy Spirit, yea, by the unspeakable gift of the Holy Ghost, that has not been revealed since the world was until now;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 2:28 (22\u201329, 49); Amos 3:7; A\u00a0of\u00a0F 1:9. TG\u00a0Mysteries of Godliness; Revelation.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Gift of.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:10 (9\u201311); 40:3. TG\u00a0Scriptures to Come Forth.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Which our forefathers have awaited with anxious expectation to be revealed in the last times, which their minds were pointed to by the angels, as held in reserve for the fulness of their glory;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 16:25; D&C 6:7 (7\u201311); 42:65 (61\u201365).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A time to come in the which nothing shall be withheld, whether there be one God or many gods, they shall be manifest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:61; 59:4; 76:7; 98:12; 101:32.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 3:30 (28\u201331); 1\u00a0Tim. 2:5.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 82:6; John 10:34; 1\u00a0Cor. 8:6 (5\u20136); D&C 76:58; Abr. 4:1 (1\u201331); 5:1 (1\u201321).",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "All thrones and dominions, principalities and powers, shall be revealed and set forth upon all who have endured valiantly for the gospel of Jesus Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 101:32.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:79. TG\u00a0Diligence; Trustworthiness.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And also, if there be bounds set to the heavens or to the seas, or to the dry land, or to the sun, moon, or stars\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 26:10 (7\u201314); 38:33 (1\u201341); Ps. 104:9 (1\u201335); Acts 17:26 (24\u201328).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "All the times of their revolutions, all the appointed days, months, and years, and all the days of their days, months, and years, and all their glories, laws, and set times, shall be revealed in the days of the dispensation of the fulness of times\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 3:4 (2\u201310). TG\u00a0Glory; God, Law of.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 151
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations.",
                        "start": 211,
                        "end": 223
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "According to that which was ordained in the midst of the Council of the Eternal God of all other gods before this world was, that should be reserved unto the finishing and the end thereof, when every man shall enter into his eternal presence and into his immortal rest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Council in Heaven.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 10:17 (17\u201321); Dan. 11:36.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Destiny of; World.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Potential to Become like Heavenly Father.",
                        "start": 233,
                        "end": 241
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 95:11; Heb. 3:11; 4:1; Alma 12:34; 3\u00a0Ne. 27:19; D&C 84:24.",
                        "start": 264,
                        "end": 268
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "How long can rolling waters remain impure? What power shall stay the heavens? As well might man stretch forth his puny arm to stop the Missouri river in its decreed course, or to turn it up stream, as to hinder the Almighty from pouring down knowledge from heaven upon the heads of the Latter-day Saints.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 8:39 (35\u201339).",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 4:35.",
                        "start": 204,
                        "end": 210
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 215,
                        "end": 223
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 12:4. TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 242,
                        "end": 251
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 242
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, there are many called, but few are chosen. And why are they not chosen?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 20:16; 22:14 (1\u201314); Luke 13:23; D&C 63:31; 95:5 (5\u20136). TG\u00a0Called of God.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because their hearts are set so much upon the things of this world, and aspire to the honors of men, that they do not learn this one lesson\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 14:18 (18\u201320).",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Selfishness; Worldliness.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Motivations.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 6:2; 2\u00a0Ne. 26:29; D&C 58:39. TG\u00a0Honor.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That the rights of the priesthood are inseparably connected with the powers of heaven, and that the powers of heaven cannot be controlled nor handled only upon the principles of righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:10. TG\u00a0Priesthood, Authority; Priesthood, Keys of; Priesthood, Oath and Covenant; Priesthood, Power of.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 137
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:30. TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 164,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That they may be conferred upon us, it is true; but when we undertake to cover our sins, or to gratify our pride, our vain ambition, or to exercise control or dominion or compulsion upon the souls of the children of men, in any degree of unrighteousness, behold, the heavens withdraw themselves; the Spirit of the Lord is grieved; and when it is withdrawn, Amen to the priesthood or the authority of that man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:13. TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals; Honesty; Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness; Pride.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:26 (26\u201328); D&C 76:111 (110\u201312).",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 167
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 18:12; D&C 1:33; 3:11; JS\u2014H 1:46. TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Loss of.",
                        "start": 275,
                        "end": 283
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, ere he is aware, he is left unto himself, to kick against the pricks, to persecute the saints, and to fight against God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 9:5; 26:14.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Persecution.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 3:5; 1\u00a0Ne. 11:35 (34\u201336).",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We have learned by sad experience that it is the nature and disposition of almost all men, as soon as they get a little authority, as they suppose, they will immediately begin to exercise unrighteous dominion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
